Package uib.teamdank.common

Interfaces and classes to describe common game elements.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ItemHolder
    An item holder is an object that can store Items in an Inventory.
    Score
    Represent an accumulated amount of points.
    Upgrade
    An upgrade specifies a set of positive changes that can be made to an Upgradeable.
    Upgradeable
    An upgradeable object, which means it can receive an Upgrade to permanently have certain properties positively changed.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Actor
    For a generic controlled actor in a game (e.g.
    Game
    Interface for a game.
    GameObject
    Represent an object in a game.
    Inventory
    A collection of Items with a maximum capacity.
    Item
    Interface for Items in the game
    ItemRecipe
    A recipe to combine two items.
